Also pasting some stuff we talked about in the interview that I also suggested to another person: - How TCP and UDP protocols work - How do online games handle a large number of players - How does a server receive and parse user input - How does a computer network work - The last interview was basically an hour long conversation about online programming. I remember talking about netcode in video games, client side prediction, replication, interpolation, lag compensation, different network architectures (client-server, peer-to-peer) and their advantages and disadvantages. - Also some basic questions about web services which I wasn't very knowledgeable about at the time. - Then there were also some standard questions about C++, different containers and algorithms in the standard library, pointers, smart pointers, etc. - They also asked about previous projects I had worked on

I suggest for now try to spend some time working on some small projects. For me personally I had worked on a mobile app and also had a simple implementation of Conway's Game of Life which helped during the recruitment process. For GPP maybe you could make some small prototype games using any game engine you like. And if you haven't had one already try to find an internship where you'll get to work on actual projects.

It'll also definitely help if you have some small projects that you've worked on since they'll you some solid content to talk about in the interviews. And a little bit of internship or work experience will be a plus as well.

Other than that as a general requirement you should definitely have some understanding of C++ and some also basic aptitude questions for the online test round (just really basic questions, nothing too crazy :) ).

Not sure about Gameplay but for Online, they'll ask you about netcode, networking(tcp, udp protocols, scaling, etc.) and web services. Some basic knowledge about docker k8s will be a plus but isn't required.

CONVERSATION TITLE: What & How of backend while scaling a popular Fantasy Game
CONTENT:
Hello Nikhil

 

2020 and 2021 have seen a sudden spike in concurrent users in the gaming world, due to the unforeseen pandemic.

 

This means the gaming companies especially multiplayer games are posing numerous backend challenges. Like ‚Äì

  • Load of managing several concurrent users hence battling instabilities
  • High costs per user while managing engaging experience
  • Difficulty in managing returns from the game while scaling up

And many more unprecedented challenges can pop up when scaling a game to success.


There is a cost-optimized solution for these issues. A popular Fantasy Cricket Game faced similar issues and we could successfully resolve all of them with our AWS managed cloud solution. Here is a glimpse of the detailed solution, 2 mins quick read case study.

 

Let us know your thoughts. Also, if you are facing any scaling challenges owing to the backend infrastructure, do write back and our AWS Cloud experts would be happy to guide and discuss the solutions.

 

Sincerely,

Mandar Navare, CEO, Flentas

CONVERSATION TITLE: SRM University MSc (Applied Data Science) Program
CONTENT:
Hi, Nikhil!


The two-year MSc (Applied Data Science) by India's Top Ranked University, SRM IST, offered in both full-time classroom and weekend hybrid program is intended for working professionals who want to pursue a career in data science and machine learning. The program will give you a platform to develop and practice the skills in concepts such as statistics, computer programming, machine learning, and artificial intelligence


  • Earn an MSc (Applied Data Science) post-graduate degree from SRM IST
  • Learn from faculty with IIT and global University pedigree and get mentored by industry experts
  • Learn advanced Applied Data Science concepts such as Enterprise Machine learning, Data Lakes, Machine learning pipelines, advanced data visualization best practices and storytelling concepts, managing Machine learning models, Artificial Intelligence domains including Natural language processing, Image, voice and video processing
  • Experience a unique and comprehensive learning approach to develop skills and competencies in machine learning, deep learning, and artificial intelligence. Total 1800+ hours of learning with 70% focus on hands-on practical & projects
  • Experiential learning through concepts and real-life case studies, simulations from Harvard Business Publishing
  • Gain the full-fledged alumni status of SRM IST and get introduced to the alumni network of SRM Group to network with peer data scientists through private online and offline events
  • Get lifetime access to the courseware on AI-based StudyNxt Platform
  • Access high Impact Career Services and Placement assistance through CareerNxt Platform


Who should take this course?


Anyone with a bachelor's degree with a minimum of 50% in 10th, 12th & graduation and passion for Data Science

Graduates working in the Data Science field and looking to grow their career

Professionals working in the Data Science industry and IT professionals with a bachelor's degree looking to transition into Data Science

Minimum 2 years of work experience is preferred for part-time and fresher may apply for the full-time classroom program.
